<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   It's true.  Metallica came to our offices here at Verant, and wouldn't
leave the lobby until something was done about the pirates, "those
remorseless, thieving bastards" they called them.  You think I'm joking,
but does it look like I'm joking, to you?<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 Question: Why do the loved-by-all Guides have the coolest graphics like
the electric sword and hot looking green plate armor while the people who are paying for the game get nothing but totems that look like a little dolly
no matter how bad-ass it should look. My point is that there are allot of graphics in the game that could be improved to make the customers happy. Instead it looks like Verant is more concerned with making those that
don't pay for the game happy, I.e guides.<P>

 Greakan of Bristlebane

<P> <P><b><i>
