<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   You know how cats will sometimes pause to lick their genitals,
holding up one hind leg as they do the deed?  Well, imagine a
three-legged cat doing that, and holding up that non-leg.  Would
that be the bomb, or what??<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 Hiya Milo.<P>

     I added this paragraph last, after I finished the whole email.  I felt
it was necessary.  I dont know if you are the right person to direct this to, but this seems a good place to start.  Before you start reading, I want to say that I know I got carried away in places and that this went far longer than I had intended... for that I apologize, and I hope you read it all.<P>

     I have an observation to make... a complaint to follow... then a solution to offer.  I acknowledge the fact that everyone generally has all three... and Im hoping to make mine coherent and intelligent.<P>

 Observation:<BR>
     The implemenation of Kunark has added many new high level dungeons and items as well as increased the level cap to 60.  Let me first say that this is a good thing.  It increases the overall 'range' of
the game.  I like it... everyone likes it... no one would take any of that
away.<P>

     To understand my complaint, I think some background is neccessary. Ive been playing EQ for about 2 months.  I have a bunch of buds who play and we all love it.  I have no single character I use all the time,
as I like different things about different classes and races and on any given day I may feel like doing something different... bashing with a Troll... commanding a pet with a Magician... just being all around good with a Druid.  My highest level char is only 10.  At the time of writing this,
Ive never been higher.  I dont get around much, except for what I see with my different chars in their home cities, and the few dungeons I venture into.  I read news, posts and guides on the web alot and check out as many screen shots as possible.  I consider EQ a hobby... not a way of life.  I wish I had some stats that showed the average level of ALL chars in EQ, as well as average playing time per day per person.  I think it would be very interesting to see how many people 'liv! e' EQ as opposed to simply play it.  Not that Im trying to critisize
either group... to each his own and such.<P>

     With that in mind, I think my complaint is best stated as coming from someone who looks up at the higher levels and knows it takes alot of effort to get there.  But that is part of the fun and enjoyment.  I think those who powerlevel are missing alot.<P>

 My Complaint:<BR>
     My complaint is simply this... I have to wait much longer to go to all the cool places, and fight all the cool MOBs and get all the cool items. Where it used to take a great deal of people of a certain level to defeat
a MOB, it now takes less people of higher levels.  Im not sure of the exact numbers, but I think you can get my point from the following example... Lets say it used to take 2 groups of level 50s to take out Lady Vox. Remember, Im only 10, so Ive never even seen her, much less camped her.  But again, this is for reference.  Now it only takes half a group of level 60s to slay her.  So now, instead of hoping to make level 50 some day, and camp Vox with a group, Ill most likely wait until level 60.  Or
if I do get to go after her at 50, Ill have to wait cause a group of 60s will
be after her.  Same for Nagafen... Maestro... the nasties in Guk... the Big Uglies in the Planes, etc.<P>

     I dont expect EQs level cap to stay at 60.  Soon Kunark will be old news, well explored by the level 50 to 60s.  New level caps will be introduced... new areas.  My fear is that someday all the Big Nasties of Now, will be soloed by the higher levels of Tomorrow.<P>

     To me, one of the many appeals of EQ is that you have to get large groups of peoples together to 'raid' large dungeons.  Im afraid that this may dissapear.  Now I know what you're thinking... this is exactly what those in Kunark have to do to kill the higher MOBs in Kunark.  A raid f level 60s is necessary to take out any Big Ugly in Kunark.  I acknowledge that.  But remember, my complaint is from that of a low level looking up.  Im afraid that EQ will always be one step ahead of those who dont 'live' EQ... who play often, but not all the time.  This is where the stats would help.  Is my concern that of the minority?... or the majority?  Is EQ designed for those who 'live' it, and not those who simply play it?  I dont have an answer, but I do have an opinion.  I suspect that the majority are people who just play it.  Ive seen to many games destroy themselves from the inside out because they cater to a smaller number of all too powerful people.  On any server where the pop! ulation is 1500-2500, how many level 50+ chars are there?  I dont know... but if you consistantly move the scales up to accomodate those people, the lower levels will never get anywhere.<P>

     Nagafen and Vox... lower Guk... the Planes... those places used to have the best MOBs and items.  When I started playing I heard of the SSOY and the FBSS and other 'godly' items.  And I wanted them!! But now, there are better items, better MOBs to fight... and now without ever had the satisfaction of attaining a SSOY or a FBSS... now I want THOSE items!  The accomplishment of attaining a SSOY is greatly lessened.  Now I want a Tree Weave!... But what is going to come out next that Ill want before I attain one of those??!!  Im a cat chasing his own tail.  Or the tails of other cats who keep outdistancing me.<P>

     Whew.  That got WAY out of hand.  I hope I didnt prattle on, and that I made sense.  In any event, I feel more comfortable now that Ive expressed myself.<P>

 My Solution:<BR>
     Next time you create a new continent like Kunark... dont put it on Norrath.  Put it on another planet.  Create a Portal for Level 55 to 60s
to go through that takes them PERMANENTLY to a new Server with higher Nasties and MOBs.  It would give everyone the ultimate goal. Then you wouldnt have to worry about high levels going back and stomping the crap out of the 'old' high level MOBs.  It would be an Ending and a Beginning to something thats never before had an ending. And people love new beginnings.  I know the developers of EQ are a very smart bunch, and it may be that this has already been thought of, in which case Im just wasting your time now.  But I think this would increase the depth of the game while maintaining the current balances.<P>

     Id like to know if this is feasible, and if its been considered at all already.<P>

 Thank you for taking the time to read this,<BR>
 Chris~

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   Anyone else stop reading this after "My complaint is simply this..." ?<P>
</font></td>
